            <div class="th-h" style="color:var(--teal);">H1</div>
            <div class="th-name">Human-Driven Commerce</div>
            <div class="th-sub" style="color:var(--teal);">Current State · Now</div>
            <p class="th-body">Commerce operations driven by human decision-making at every layer. Brand, campaign, merchandising, and service decisions made by people, informed by data. Most organisations operate here — but the window is narrowing faster than most acknowledge.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="th-item">
            <div class="th-h" style="color:var(--gold);">H2</div>
            <div class="th-name">AI-Augmented Commerce</div>
            <div class="th-sub" style="color:var(--gold);">Transition · Now–3 Years</div>
            <p class="th-body">Human decisions augmented by AI recommendation, prediction, and automation. AI handles pattern recognition and optimisation; humans handle judgment and strategy. The critical window where competitive advantage is being built — or permanently ceded.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="th-item">
            <div class="th-h" style="color:var(--amber);">H3</div>
            <div class="th-name">Autonomous Commerce</div>
            <div class="th-sub" style="color:var(--amber);">Target State · 3–7 Years</div>
            <p class="th-body">Commerce operations that run autonomously within defined strategic parameters. Humans set strategy, values, and constraints; AI executes the commerce system. The 12P™ Framework is architectured to operate — and compound — in this state.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
